Job Category: Information Technology; Technology

With over six decades of business and technical experience in the mining, energy, and infrastructure sectors, we understand that challenges are changing rapidly in every industry. We respond quickly with solutions that are smarter, more efficient, and innovative. We draw upon our 9,000 staff with experience in over 150 countries to challenge the status quo and create positive change for our clients, our employees, and the communities we serve.

Scope of Position

Hatch is seeking a Sr. Data Scientist for a key role in its Data Science business. We are looking for a creative problem-solver that is motivated by the desire to deliver innovative, efficient and sustainable solutions with improved business outcomes. The successful candidate will have an opportunity to work on leading edge digital technologies.

Working in the Global Data Science Center of Excellence, you will provide technical guidance in the development of Data Science-based products that deliver clear value for our clients. You have deep technical knowledge and a history of assisting organizations create solutions using Advanced Analytics/ Machine Learning/ Data Science technologies.

Primary Responsibilities:
Be the Subject Matter Expert (SME) on Machine Learning/ Advanced Analytics technologies to both internal Hatch teams and external Hatch clients;
Communicate and coordinate effectively with internal Hatch stakeholders and external clients to ensure models & results are well understood and incorporated into their business processes;
Process, cleanse, and verify the integrity of data used for analysis
Identify, interpret and communicate meaningful insights from large data and metadata sources to clients and internal interdisciplinary teams;
Identify opportunities to improve data collection and management procedures
Select the most appropriate Machine Learning methods for specific applications, validate and deploy data analytics models to achieve business results;
Demonstrate thought leadership through company blogs, articles, white papers, conference presentations, etc.

Qualifications (Required):
Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics or equivalent from an accredited University and 5+ years of experience developing and applying innovative data-driven models in industrial and business settings;
Experience in quantitative analysis / research of large, complex data sets;
Excellent knowledge and experience applying machine learning techniques and algorithms such as k-NN, LSTM, Naïve Bayes, SVM, Decision Forests, Neural Networks, multivariate analysis (PCA/ PLS), etc.
Excellent scripting and programming skills in common data science analytical/programming tools (e.g., Python) and data visualization tools (e.g., PowerBI);

Assets:
Experience with deep learning frameworks (Keras, TensorFlow, PyTorch) and cloud technologies (e.g., AWS, GCP, MS Azure) is desirable.
A postgraduate degree in mathematics, statistics, computer science, engineering or another quantitative field;

Skills:
Keenly interested in creating innovative solutions to solve challenging industrial problems;
Demonstrated ability to work both collaboratively and independently when appropriate;
Ability to build relationships and effectively influence colleagues, clients and stakeholders;
Excellent communication, interpersonal and teamwork skills.

We are committed to fostering a workforce in each of our locations that reflects the diversity of the communities in which we operate. Hatch is an Equal Opportunity Employer that considers employment applicants without regard to age, race, colour, national origin, citizenship, religion, creed, sex, sexual orientation, marital status, disability or any other protected status. If you have any special needs requirements, please let us know. We will do our utmost to accommodate, in accordance with applicable local legislation.

POSITION SUMMARY

Reporting to the Manager, Fees in the Office of the Registrar, the Business Data Analyst - Tuition and Fees works closely with all academic schools and many non-academic departments to establish processes and complete transactions as they relate to the establishment of student tuition, related incidental fees and all other fees collected through the Office of the Registrar in the Banner Student
system. This requires the incumbent to understand and interpret Ministry policy related to tuition and fees; have a comprehensive understanding of accounts receivable practices; maintain and ensure accuracy of the Banner tuition and fee tables; and process fees related to student accounts and the collection of student account receivables. Under the guidance of the Manager, the incumbent will work independently and is required to make decisions that can impact student finances, academic school and department processes and ultimately the College’s financial position. The Business Data Analyst - Tuition and Fees is required to work college wide to collect and maintain reports and documents such as the Master Humber College Fee Document, to produce a stable, clear and transparent fee environment. The incumbent is expected to collaborate frequently with the Fees, Audit and Reporting Coordinator, the
Records and Registration Officers and Financial Services to resolve any issues as they relate to fees, the enrollment and financial audits effecting, student records and registration.

QUALIFICATIONS

The successful incumbent obtains a 3 year diploma/ degree or equivalent in the following fields of study: Accounting, Commerce, Business Administration, Computer Science or related program of study, and is working towards an accounting designation, in the final levels of certification for: CGA, CM, CA or CPA.

The incumbent must have a minimum of 3 years' related work experience working in student fee collection or accounting.The incumbent should demonstrate the following:
Strong knowledge of financial statements, receipts, payments, general accounting procedures and internal controls;
Strong analytical and problem solving skills;
Superior communication skills with the ability to explain complex processes;
Sound understanding of the post-secondary system;
Proficiency in the use of Microsoft Office Suite, especially Microsoft Excel;
Demonstrated proficiency in student information systems, especially relational databases;
Ability to work in a highly automated environment Leadership skills and the ability to work independently;
Ability to guide and motivate a team.

